  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (faults-physical gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. The pump is deployed in continuous in vivo extracorporeal circuits during prolonged surgical procedures and post-operative support runs lasting up to 14 days; the operating environment includes vibration from transport, thermal cycling in perfusion cabinets, and progressive bearing wear over extended duty cycles. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Fault tolerance for sensor failure, actuator wear, and electrical anomalies is documented elsewhere.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cpb-hemolysis-mrl2",
